                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Argues that the recent apportionment of Pennsylvania House and Senate
                    districts is unfair to the Democrats. Franklin County was assigned only one
                    member of the House and, with Adams County, one member of the Senate.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
